TY  - JOUR
TI  - Limit Pricing, Uncertain Entry, and the Entry Lag
AU  - De Bondt, Raymond R.
AB  - [An established seller's pre-entry price policy is studied under the assumption that this policy affects the probability of entry and that rivals need an entry lag to make their entries effective. The analysis is conducted using a modified Kamien-Schwartz limit pricing model.]
